@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

@{MS "Introduction"}

AView is a multiview enhancement. You ask why you need AView? Every file needs a datatype. Many
datatypes aren´t available or not very effective.@{par}

You want to view a JPG picture and your prefered viewer? No problem! AView allows to specify a
viewer for every file format.@{par}

AView detects your file and runs the specified program or tool.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "System requirements"

@{MS "System requirements"}

AView (should work) works on all Amigas with OS 2.0 or higher.@{par}

Some functions are not available under 2.0, because they require OS3.x+ (MemoryPools, ...)@{par}

From OS2.1 on AView is able to work multilingual.@{par}

If you want to run programs by using the WB-Mode you need the WBStart.library V2.x. This library is
under development of Stefan Becker and is available on Aminet.@{par}

That`s all!@{par}

@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Feature List"

@{MS "Feature List"}

@{jcenter}

Local support@{par}

Kickstart 2.04 or higher is required.@{par}

Programmed in Commodore Styleguide@{par}

All adjustments are possible per Gadtools-GUI@{par}

Different versions for different Kickstart versions.@{par}

100% Assembler@{par}

Online help@{par}

Pre defined file types for an easy configuration.@{par}

Allows to specify own file types.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Distribution" "Distribution"

@{MS "Distribution"}

This program may be published on every public medium, as long as all files in the archive are
unchanged. If this medium is a CD I expect a free copy. (Aminet-CDs excluded)@{par}

@{b}AView is giftware.@{ub}@{par}

I expect from everybody, who uses AView regularly, to register send in a small gift.
I think this does not hurt anybody, and I will have more fun to integrate new features or write a
new game.@{par}

@{b}I am not liable for injuries or data loss caused by AView. The use of AView is on your own
responsibility !!!@{ub}@{par}

@endnode
@node "Kickstart" "Quick start"

@{MS "Quick start"}

After installing AView you should run AViewPrefs. Some file types are installed by default and are
ready to be modified.@{par}

If you want to include new types, then use the @{"select" link "APMaSele"} gadget. A new
@{"requester" link "GeLw"} opens and allows to choose one of the pre defined file types.@{par}

After selecting one listview in the @{"main" link "APMa"} window you are able to open the
@{"Edit" link "Edit"} window by using the "Return"-Key. It is also possible to choose via double clicking on
one entry.@{par}

The @{"Edit" link "Edit"} window allows to specify the command. This command will be started any
time AView recognizes the specified file type. Use @{"%f" link "EditComm"} to define the position of
the file name. AView replaces this pattern automatically during operation.@{par}

Repeat this actions until all file types are defined.@{par}

@endnode
@node "HowToInstall" "How to Install AView"

@{MS "How to Install AView"}

Please use the original Commodore Installer to install AView.@{par}

There is also an option to deinstall a prevous installation.@{par}

@endnode
@node "AView" "AView"

@{MS "AView"}

This is the main program and needed for daily usage. You are able to run AView via CLI, Workbench or
AppIcon, by using Toolmanager or something like that.@{par}

@{MS "Run via CLI"}

This is the aview template:@{par}

"AView @{"Name/M" link "PATTNAME"}, @{"ARG=To=From/K" link "PATTARG"}, @{"All/S" link "PATTALL"},
@{"SC=SetComment/S" link "PATTSC"}, @{"SD=ShowDetect/S" link "PATTSD"}, @{"Debug/S" link "PATTDEBUG"}"

@{MS "Run via Workbench"}

Under normal conditions it is not useful, because AView isn´t able to get file names. AView opens a
ASL-file requester.

@{MS "Toolmanager and ..."}

By using tools like Toolmanager or something like that you are able to put AView on Docks, AppIcons,
Menus and many more. AView will view all files without any problems.@{par}

But it is required to define your prefered @{"file types" link "APMa"}. This procedure is required
only once.

@endnode
@node "History" "History"

@{MS "History"}

This text is telling the story of AView like a diary.

 @{MC "0.95B"}

First working beta version.

 @{MC "0.96B"}

Small changes.@{par}
Manual updated and AView adjusted to allow the new features of the preference window

 @{MC "0.97B"}

Small CurrentDir bug fixed. This bug causes crashes when using "mfs-handler" and "AmiCDFS". It seems
that SystemTagList is doing some strange things by using the "NP_Current" tag that causes such
problems. "df0:" it self didn`t make any problems. AViewPrefs is sorting all entries automatically.

 @{MC "0.98B"}

BUGFIX: Small @{"Match" link "CO_Match"} bug fixed.@{par}
FEATURE: Debug mode implemented.@{par}
FEATURE: Small prefs changes.

 @{MC "0.99B"}

Some internal adjustments.

 @{MC "1.00"}

FEATURE: @{"ShowDetect" link "PATTSD"} feature implemented. (requested by Andreas Boerner)@{par}
BUGFIX: Empty files caused problems. (reported by Andreas Boerner)@{par}
FEATURE: France catalogs included. (Thanks to Jerome Chesnot)@{par}
FEATURE: Enlarged string gadgets. (requested by Andreas Boerner)

 @{MC "1.01"}

@{"NOT" link "CO_Not"} Command implemented. (requested by Andreas Boerner)

 @{MC "1.02"}

Small sourcecode optimisations.

 @{MC "1.03"}

"1" and "0" are now valid commands, so it is possible to use AView to solve mathematical problems. I
needed this "feature" to check the internal commands without using test files for recognition.

 @{MC "1.04"}

Some Manual adjustments.

 @{MC "1.05"}

It is possible to define Lha if DMS is already defined. (reported by Andreas Boerner)

 @{MC "1.06"}

New Command @{"FILESIZE" link "CO_FileSize"}. It allows to detect a file by its size.

 @{MC "1.07"}

BUGFIX: No longer endless loops. Thrust me! 5 hours of intensive debugging. It wasn`t possible to
debug this direct, because the bug wasn`t reproducable. I had to debug a running task. (reported by
Andreas Boerner, Silke Bormann and me)

 @{MC "1.08"}

Kickstart-Types implemented and @{"ShowDetect" link "PATTSD"} function fixed.

 @{MC "1.09"}

Keyfile-Support.

